    • regionsForLocation

      protected List<Region> regionsForLocation(Location location)
      Returns:
      The list of regions that contain the given location (in the world graph, this will always be a single cell).

      NOTE: Historically, regions could nest to allow nested administrative borders like states and countries (and that code, while no longer used, should still work, albeit VERY inefficiently), but now regions are non-overlapping, non-nested grid cells in the world graph)
